This paper is primarily focused on image generation using deep generative models, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of self- and semi-supervised learning techniques, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of Fréchet Inception Distance (FID) as a metric for evaluating the quality of generated images, which is commonly used in graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM) research.
